4.40	Climate_of_Colombia	Climate of Colombia	The Climate of Colombia is characterized for being tropical and isothermal as a result of its geographical location near the Equator presenting variations within five natural regions and depending on the altitude, temperature, humidity, winds and rainfall. Each region maintains an average temperature throughout the year only presenting variables determined by precipitation during a rainy season caused by the Intertropical Convergence Zone.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Bogota_hailstorm.jpg/220px-Bogota_hailstorm.jpg
